      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(media-understanding): resolve image model input from catalog, preserve explicit text-only (#92104)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix the image/pdf tool failing with \"Model does not support images\" when `models.providers` or agent `models.json` entries omit the `input` field. The fix lives in the shared model resolver (`resolveModelAsync`) so ALL consumers benefit, not just media-understanding.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nIn `resolveProviderModelInput`, when the user omits `input` from their model config, the default is `[\"text\"]`. The inline provider match shadows the bundled catalog where the same model is registered with `[\"text\",\"image\"]`. The resolution chain returns the text-only inline model, and downstream image consumers reject it.\n\n**Fix**: In `resolveModelAsync`, after model resolution, merge `input` capabilities from the bundled static catalog — but only when the user did NOT explicitly declare an `input` array in either `cfg.models.providers` or agent-local `models.json`. This is adjacent to the existing `mediaInput` merge logic.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: Models with omitted `input` in models.providers or models.json → catalog fills `[\"text\",\"image\"]` → image tool proceeds. Models with explicit user-specified `input` → preserved unchanged.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux x64 (RHEL 8), Node.js v24.13.1, pnpm v11.2.2, openclaw at 79d7defd0b\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```\npnpm test -- --run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.test.ts\npnpm test -- --run src/media-understanding/image.test.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix** — terminal output:\n\nModel resolver tests (real `resolveModelAsync` path):\n```\n Tests  107 passed (107)\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n Duration  47.21s\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 56.35s\n```\n\nImage understanding tests (mocked `resolveModelAsync`, zero regressions from revert):\n```\n Tests  26 passed (26)\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n Duration  9.51s\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 18.69s\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**:\n- `input` omitted from config → catalog supplies `[\"text\",\"image\"]` → all consumers see image capability\n- `input: [\"text\"]` in `cfg.models.providers` → preserved, catalog NOT consulted\n- `input: [\"text\"]` in agent `models.json` (`providers` shape) → preserved\n- Fix lives in shared resolver — no image-runtime-specific file I/O or code paths\n- 107 + 26 = 133 tests pass with zero regressions\n\n**Production change**:\n```\nsrc/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.ts  |  +78 lines\nsrc/media-understanding/image.ts           |  reverted to original\nsrc/media-understanding/image.test.ts      |  reverted to original\n```\n\nThe change adds `hasExplicitModelInput` (checks cfg + models.json) and merges catalog `input` in `resolveModelAsync`'s existing `allowBundledStaticCatalogFallback` block.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end gateway with live API keys (requires real credentials).\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm test -- --run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.test.ts` — 107/107\n- [x] `pnpm test -- --run src/media-understanding/image.test.ts` — 26/26\n- [x] Fix in shared resolver — all existing model tests exercise the new code path\n- [x] No new file I/O in image runtime — image tests unchanged\n\n---\n*AI-assisted: built with Claude Code*\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-92104-v3",
